(184, NULL, NULL, 192, 'A000093327E', 'Lead', 'nil', 'KENYAN', '3507879', 'BOX 13962 -00800, Westlands', 'NAIROBI', 'NAIROBI', '0722275806', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; <span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Key Qualifications</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Dr. Reardon Olubayo is a career Research and Development Consultant with a wealth&nbsp; of experience in Agriculture and Livestock industry for over 30 years.He worked for Ministry of Agriculture and Livestock Development for 14 years before joining the Kenya Agricultural Research Institute (KARI) as a Senior Research Scientist where he worked for 5 years. Following this successful career, the International Centre of Insect Physiology and Ecology (<strong>ICIPE</strong>) employed Dr. Olubayo as a Research Scientist where he worked for 5 years before embarking on a career as a consultant. He has published more than 34 scientific papers in reputable both local and international journals.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Dr. REARDON OLUBAYO was registered as an EIA Lead Expert w.e.f.&nbsp; February, 2004. NEMA registration No. 0021.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: small;\">He is a Research Scientist and formerly worked for Kenya Agricultural&nbsp; &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: small;\">Research&nbsp; Institute (KARI) and the International Center for Insect&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: small;\">Physiology and Ecology (ICIPE).</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: small;\">He now works as a Development Consultant in Agriculture and Environment&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: small;\">and carries&nbsp; EIA/EA assignments&nbsp; regularly.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r