(565, NULL, NULL, 611, 'N/a', 'Lead', 'Kennkamau2009@gmail.com ', 'Kenyan ', '11316294', 'P.o Box 79268-00200', 'Nairobi ', 'Nairobi ', '0724652000', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: small;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Re: Profile for Kenneth Kamau Ndungu &ndash; Environment and Social Expert</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: small;\">Ken holds a Bachelor of Science Degree (Chemistry) from the University of Nairobi as well as a master&rsquo;s degree in Business Administration from Jomo Kenyatta University of Agriculture and Technology.&nbsp; Ken was registered by NEMA (National Environmental Management Authority) as a Lead Audit Expert in March 2004 and thus has over 15 years of experience in carrying out Environmental Impact Assessments and Environmental audits.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: small;\">Ken is also trained Auditor in ISO 14001 Environmental Management Systems and has implemented ISO 14001 EMS and ISO 9001 Quality Management Systems for several organizations in Kenya and South Africa.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: small;\">Ken has worked in several infrastructure projects as project environmentalist and these have mainly been in road construction, power generation, upstream oil and gas and abattoir construction. Most of these projects have been funded by World Bank, IFC or African Development Fund (ADB) and these projects have had components that required adherence to the IFC performance standards or environmental and social safeguards of the donor.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: small;\">Ken has experience working in community liaison which involved working with the community to address emerging social issues and ensure that the project had social licence and acceptance to operate in the area.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: small;\">Ken also has over ten years manufacturing experience having worked for several organizations such as Coca Cola (Beverages), Gas Naturel Fenosa (Power Generation), Tetra Pak (Paper conversion) and Nutro manufacturing (Fortified Blended Foods). In all these organizations, Ken worked as the Quality Assurance Manager hence giving him a good understanding of manufacturing processes, procedure writing, auditing factories, and implementing World Class Manufacturing practices.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: small;\">Ken&rsquo;s latest project involved providing Environmental Advisory services for an oil and gas company operating in Northern Kenya and the advisory services included establishing&nbsp; regulatory and permitting requirements for operating an oil and gas facility, ensuring that the project adhered to IFC performance standards, ensuring the project was permitted by both NEMA and the County Government and liaising with government and non-government actors to ensure sustainability of the project.</span></p>'),
