(719, NULL, NULL, 781, 'N/A', 'Lead', 'cachieng@students.uonbi.ac.ke', 'Kenyan', '13379165', 'Africa Nazarene University P.O. Box 53067  00200 Nairobi', 'Nairobi', 'Kenya', '+254(0)722821171', '<p>My name is Celline Achieng&rsquo; currently teaching in the Department of Environment and Natural Resource Management. I hold a Master&rsquo;s degree in Environmental Studies from Kenyatta University, Kenya.</p>\r\n<p>In my early years of employment, I worked with the National Museums of Kenya as a volunteer in the herbarium department before joining the African Centre for Technology Studies (ACTS); a Policy Analysis Institution in natural resource management as a Research Assistant.</p>\r\n<p>I also worked with the African Wildlife Foundation (AWF) as a Community-Based Natural Resources Management (CBNRM) Project and Learning Officer for East Africa. While holding this position, I looked at what had worked and what had not worked, that is, lessons learnt for Community-Based projects in wildlife inhabited areas. I also documented best practices in CBNRM.</p>\r\n<p>Besides, I worked with the East African Wild Life Society (EAWLS) as a Project Coordinator of a project geared towards empowering communities to engage in formulation of policies and laws governing natural resources at county level. To ensure this involvement, I participated in the formation of four (4) County Natural Resource Networks in Samburu, Laikipia, Nakuru and Kwale Counties. I also worked with Charcoal Producer Associations in Kwale and Kajiado Counties by ensuring that they adopt alternative sources of livelihoods. This was to deter them from charcoal production or ensure use of sustainable ways of charcoal production.</p>\r\n<p>In all the positions I have held, I have had a hands-on experience in working on environmental projects hence my vast knowledge in environmental management. I also coordinated a national wildlife forum called Kenya Wildlife Conservation Forum (KWCF) which is hosted at the EAWLS for six years.</p>\r\n<p>Furthermore, I am a Lead Expert number 2873 registered with the National Environment Management Authority (NEMA) and has undertaken a number of Environmental Impact Assessments and Environmental Audits (EA).</p>'),
