(800, NULL, NULL, 870, 'P051124550Q', 'Lead', '', 'Kenyan', '27501160', '1709', 'Kitale', 'Trans-Nzoia', '0711813483', '<p>Currently registered as a Ph.D. at the University of Nairobi, Department of Environmental and Biosystems Engineering. Holder of Msc. in environmental and Biosystems engineering (irrigation and water resources option) B.Sc. Degree in Environmental and Biosystems Engineering (Upper second Class Honors), from the University of Nairobi.</p>\r\n<p>I am registered as associate expert with National Environmental Management Authority (NEMA) and a member of Environment Institute of Kenya (EIK).</p>\r\n<p>I have good knowledge of EMCA 1999 and all NEMA Regulations, and other Kenyan Environmental Laws. I am as well conversant with the IFC EHS Guidelines for various sectors and as well conversant to IFC ESPSs &amp; OPs, IFC RAP guidelines.</p>\r\n<p>I have three years&rsquo; experience working as an environmental expert. I have been involved in proposal writing, field works and report writing in the same field of environment and in the water sector. Some of the major works include development of ESIA and RAP report for Marsabit &ndash; Loiyangalani 400kv power transmission line, ESIA and RAP Gilgil &ndash; Thika -Nairobi East &ndash; Konza 400kV power transmission line, ESIA and RAP for Isiolo &ndash; Marsabit 220kV power transmission line, ESIA and RAP for Murang&rsquo;a water project and as well ESIA for Nyeri sewerage sytem etc. I was recently involved with the development of Kenya National Environmental Performance Index (EPI) 2017 National Environment and Management Authority (NEMA).</p>\r\n<p>I have also in Kenya and the neighbouring country of Sudan working as an agricultural value chain expert in the development of Risk Sharing and Financial Mechanism (RSFM). Also worked in Uganda in transboundary project of development of sub-catchment development plan of middle Malaba and lower Sio River with Nile Basin Initiative (NBI), Lukhuna irrigation demonstration in Manafwa District, Uganda and Chepkaraam Suswo and Stabicha irrigation demonstrations in Cheptais and Sirisia District, Kenya. I was also involved in rehabilitation of hydromet networks and monitoring and evaluation of the same, data analysis and management of SMM database but also liaison with Water Resources Management Authority /Lake Victoria North Catchment Area and other key stakeholders within the Sio Malaba Malakisi River Basin</p>\r\n<p>I am currently working on the development of Bomet water master plan as a team leader with the objective to provide a strategy and a roadmap for planning activities and projects for future investments in water supply in Bomet County. To achieve this we are using QGIS and QSWAT. I have also worked as a project manager in several projects with varied scope including design of Nyeri sewer line and Muranga pipeline as well as development of environmental and social impact analysis reports (ESIA) for the projects.</p>\r\n<p>I have knowledge and experience in using hydrological models such as QSWAT and use of QGIS. Some other software&rsquo;s are CLIMWAT and CROPWAT, R Software and SPSS. I am also good in all the Microsoft applications such as MS word, Excel, Power point, MS Project and Visio.</p>\r\n<p>I have also worked as a part time lecturer in Machakos University taking soil and water conservation and Irrigation and Drainage Courses. Worked as a research assistant in Kenyatta University taking solid and structural mechanics I &amp; II and in Technical University of Kenya taking Professional Engineering Practice and Environmental and Social Assessment and Audit.</p>'),
