(833, NULL, NULL, 907, 'NA', 'Associate', 'Mabiaziz.aa@gmail.com', 'Kenyan', '25833632', 'P.O Box 105672', 'Nairobi', 'Kenya', '0720743455', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Abdiaziz Ali is Natural Resource Management (NRM) and Monitoring and Evaluation (M&amp;E) expert with over 7 years professional experience working in the Horn of Africa region. Over the years, Abdiaziz has acquired vast knowledge in NRM and M&amp;E, through hands on experience, in designing and implementing project and program evaluation, Environmental and Social Impact Assessment, and environmental Audit. He had variously undertaken consulting services in Kenya and Somalia working with a team of distinguished professional and diverse communities.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),
(834, NULL, NULL, 908, 'NA', 'Lead', 'sndiwa@krc.co.ke', 'Kenyan', '23856123', 'P.O. BOX 2612-80100', 'MOMBASA', 'MOMBASA', '0722532981', '<p>A healthy environment is a foundation of human life. Our environment is fragile and requires the effort of each and everyone to protect it from depletion and eventual loss hence denying future generation from benefiting from it. There are numerous development projects currently ongoing and their impacts on the environment are irreversible. EIA as a requirement under the EMCA 1999 has in the recent past raised more queries on its importance in safeguarding our environment. EIA should help developers make a clear decision on whether to commit finances on the project based on environmental sustainability and social acceptability. Lately, there are many multi-billion projects that critical environmental concerns have been raised by stakeholders yet these projects have EIAs and licenses issued. The importance of EIA needs to be emphasized. There is a need to align with best practice so as biodiversity is safeguarded. </p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),
(835, NULL, NULL, 910, 'P051326959Q', 'Lead', 'francisasunah@gmail.com', 'Kenya', '7395387', 'BOX 9191', 'KISUMU', 'KISUMU', '+254722301038', '<p>Francis is a 56 year old Kenyan Environmentalist/ Water Resources Engineer and hydrology professional with a Master of Engineering degree.<br /><br />He is currently working as a Technical Advisor with Watersan Consultants &amp; Developers Ltd, a Water and Environmental Sector and general development consultancy. Francis has&nbsp;over 32 years result oriented post- qualification experience in water and sanitation sector and general development planning; project development, management, financing and administration as well as over 19 years experience in environmental matters; as Lead Expert with the Kenyan focal agency, National Environment Management Agency (NEMA).</p>\r\n<p>Francis is a professional member of the Environmental Institute of Kenya (EIK).&nbsp;<br /><br /><br /></p>');
