(836, NULL, NULL, 911, 'N/A', 'Associate', 'dianamwaura200@gmail.com', 'Kenyan', '32558924', '1805', 'Nairobi', 'Nairobi', '0700201790', '<p>Diana Mwaura is an environmentalist, interested in driving Environment compliance, Environment Sustainability, Environment project management, and enforcing Environmental policies &amp; legislations. She is an active member of the Environment Institute of Kenya and a registered Environment impact assessment (EIA) associate expert of the National Environment Management Authority (NEMA).</p>\r\n<p>She is a graduate in BSc Environment planning &amp; management from Kenyatta University and holds a Diploma in project management from Kenya Institute of Management.</p>\r\n<p>She is currently an Environment lead at Kenya Breweries Limited<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">,</span>&nbsp;where Diana set, communicate and drive implementation of Environment sustainability targets &amp; action plans on (Energy, Greenhouse gases, water Waste to landfill, effluent treatment and (BOD)Biological oxygen demand discharged) to meet targets and oversee their delivery.&nbsp;Enforce the required Environmental compliance to legislation;&nbsp;Ensure Implementation of Food Safety, Quality, Environment, and Safety Management Systems according to FSSC 22000, ISO 9001, ISO14001 and BS 18001 requirements respectively;&nbsp;Benchmark, draw, implement and manage KBL Environment performance program and&nbsp;Embed Environmental requirements in the day to day operations.</p>\r\n<p>Diana key achievements include;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Sustained Zero<strong> waste </strong>to landfill for the last 2 years driven by recycling and re-use.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Delivered ZERO</strong> environmental breaches, compliance issues, restoration orders, improvement, and prohibition notices&nbsp;have been issued.</li>\r\n<li>100% <strong>compliance</strong> with the Nairobi Water &amp; Sewerage Company (NWSC) discharge parameters.</li>\r\n<li><strong>100% compliance </strong>with internal &amp; external audits.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Successful </strong>review site Environmental Aspects and implementation of Environment management system on-site in accordance with<strong> ISO 14001:2015</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>100% compliance to statutory and regulatory obligations&nbsp;</strong>through renewing licenses, compliance to legal register requirements, permits compliance, and conducting Environment audits.</li>\r\n<li>Collaborated with the KBL Corporate Relations team and held several successful Corporate Responsibility initiatives, among them, are road clean-ups and led supply in planting <strong>over 1000 trees</strong> in &nbsp;Njukiri-Embu county and Wanjarere-Muranga county.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>She Led KBL to achieve Environment compliance (zero breaches), achieved zero waste to landfill, led sustainable initiatives on water and energy KPI which led to Kenya breweries being recognized by Kenya Association of manufacturers and FOODEX.</p>\r\n<p>Among other distinctions in the field. Diana participates in Environmental protection discussions held by the Environmental Institute of Kenya and the National Environmental Management Authority.</p>\r\n<p>Diana is a form Nairobi-Kenya. Please email&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:dianamwaura500@gmail.com\">dianamwaura500@gmail.com</a><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>to contact Diana.</p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>'),
