(844, NULL, NULL, 921, 'A005262594', 'Associate', 'okechowino@gmail.com;', 'KENYAN', '22850924', '27146- 00100', 'NAIROBI', 'NAIROBI', '0721852298', '<p>Hello, I\'m a 35 year old Kenyan by birth (born in Garbatulllah, Isiolo). Through my upbringing and current life, love for environment has always been a main stay. My first field work was in Amboseli national park in 1994, where I was part of a delegation of students picked from across the country, to plant trees. In line with the late Prof. Wangari Mathai\'s word sof a humming bird, I first do the much I can. It may be a little, but my duty to the human race is to start by doing what I can.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>in 2006, together with my campus room mate, we started a waste management company, \"BINS ON WHEELS\" in an effort to contribute to proper waste management and disposal. The model we envisioned was to empower Nairobians to be able to \"treat their waste with taste\" because this would make recycling or re-using easier and cheaper. However, we ran into a few challenges and the company did not take flight as we both sought employment and the issue of cartels was too much do deal with.</p>\r\n<p>In a world of choices, I chose to study environmental management (First choice) at Makerere University. Environmental management has many areas and I will not take this time to expound on it, but it is the reason why I am still advocating for action for climate change, proper waste management and disposal, reduction, re-use, recyling, gender and environment, philosophy, biodiversity and ecosystems (Just to mention but a tip of the iceberg) .</p>\r\n<p>Mainstreaming of environmental issues or education and empowerment in everyday agenda is a life time\'s work. We must change how we do things so that the very environment we depend on does not suffer harm. Some damages are irreversible, for example, when global warming contributes to the extinction of species and loss of biodiversity. We must actively participate in efforts at all levels to inform developments, ideas, projects and any endeavour.</p>\r\n<p>I am an environmentalist through and through and I ca make a contribution as part of teams that are working to best management of the environment.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),
