(1280, NULL, NULL, 1389, 'A001792597L ', 'Lead', '', 'KENYAN', '8353731', 'P.O.BOX 171-90300', 'WOTE', 'MAKUENI', '0710251308', '<p align=\"justify\">Mr. Joseph Kamula Muia is a holder of Bsc.Agricultural Engineering for the last 28&nbsp;years and has worked with the Ministry of Agriculture in different capacities for 25 years at the Ministry headquarters and in three districts i.e February 1993 to September 1997 in Turkana District, September 1997 to June 2005 in Makueni District and from July 2005 to November 2017 in &nbsp;Garissa District giving him a wide experience.&nbsp;He is currently based at the Ministry of Agriculture, State Department for Crop Development headquarters in Nairobi.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">During his work in the three districts, he has &nbsp;been deployed in the capacities of District Irrigation Engineer/Soil And Water Conservation Officer, District Irrigation Engineer, District Coffee Factory Engineer, Monitoring And Evaluation Speciallist for Kenya Agricultural Productivity and Agribusiness Project ( Phase I &amp;II) in Garissa District, and &nbsp;Departmental HIV/AIDS Control Officer.&nbsp;He is currently heading the Soil and Water Conservation management services at the &nbsp;State Department for Crop Development headquarters.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">Key work duties entailed&nbsp;deputizing the KAPAP Project Coordinator at Garissa County, training of staff and beneficiary farmer groups, coordination of staff performing extension service delivery activities and conducting various surveys &nbsp;like baseline, soil conservation catchment, water plan surveys&nbsp;and coordination of environmental screening of community projects. Other duties include conducting&nbsp;Broad Based Surveys/Participatory Rural Appraisal, Project Impact assessment, Project Evaluation and Adoption survey &nbsp;for project cycle management and guiding the development of business plans for agricultural Production Value Chains- (beef, tomato and milk) and their upgrading into cooperatives within Garissa County.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">During the entire working period, he continuously dealt with projects that use &nbsp;natural resources like soil and water in agricultural enterprises both in crop and livestock produciton. Ensuring environmental safeguards has been a key aspect during project planning &nbsp;and implementation based on project screening and environmental impact assessments.</p>'),
