(1504, NULL, NULL, 1635, 'N/a', 'Associate', '', 'Kenyan', '13602382', '6895-00100', 'Nairobi', 'Kenya', '0723462394', '<p>Mr. Walter Ouma Onditi is a Management Information System and Monitoring &amp; Evaluation specialist with over 15 years&rsquo; of work experience. Mr Onditi is a Certified Trainer with Humanitarian Leadership Academy (HLA), UK and National Industrial Training Institute (NITA). He has strong hands on experience in both M&amp;E and ICT, coupled with outstanding skills in development of M&amp;E systems and Frameworks, both IT-Based and non IT-based, data analysis, project programming, report writing, change management, Knowledge Management and strategic plan development and implementation for various levels of clients/ stakeholders.</p>\r\n<p>Mr. Onditi has been a consultant for World Bank supporting Integrated Financial Management Information System (IFMIS) and Salaries and Review Commission (SRC) as an M&amp;E Specialist supporting M&amp;E system and framework development, implementation and reporting on project&rsquo;s progress status alongside other M&amp;E processes including capacity building. He has also worked for USAID-AHADI in reviewing the implementation of Revenue Collection and Management System in County governments of Kenya towards strengthening and sustaining revenue collection.</p>\r\n<p>Currently Mr Onditi consults for the Kenya Institute of Management and Kiambu County Assembly supporting M&amp;E Capacity aligned to the respective institutions mandates. Besides, he&rsquo;s a lecturer at KIM and the Jomo Kenyatta University on part time basis, both in MIS and Project Management. He has also consulted for Kenya Institute of Curriculum Development in the development of ICT curriculum besides being an examiner for Kenya National Examination Council (KNEC). Onditi has also been instrumental in design and implementation of M&amp;E curriculum frameworks in a number of institutions in Kenya. He also supported the development of Emergency Preparedness and Response certification programme, a course being implemented by Kenya Institute of Management (KIM) and Save the Children, UK.</p>\r\n<p>Other previous consultancies included National gender Commission on short term assignment offering advisories services, training and development of planning tools amongst other consultancy assignments with specific interest in Project Management, M&amp;E and ICT. Mr. Onditi has had a 2 years work experience with UN-HABITAT as a Consultant in the design and implementation of Monitoring and Evaluation Database &amp; Evaluation Website aimed at tracking implementation status of Management recommendations. For 4 years Mr Onditi worked as a Monitoring &amp; Evaluation / Management Information Systems Officer with International Funds for Agriculture Development (IFAD), developing and implementing various Monitoring and Evaluation assignments for informed decision.</p>\r\n<p>Mr Onditi has a wealth of experience working with communities in Kenya developing community Based -M&amp;E tools for capturing and reporting on short and long term results. Onditi has been engaged in assessment of agriculture value chain projects across Counties in Kenya. Therefore has understanding of players and actors along the agriculture value chain. For 15 years, Mr Onditi has had continuous work experience as a consultant in ICT, Trainings and capacity building for both for private sector, NGO&rsquo;s and governments in Kenya. Out of work experience, 8 years has been in supporting clients&rsquo; implements M&amp;E systems including offering ICT solutions for various organizations.</p>\r\n<p>Mr Onditi strong competencies are in Monitoring and Evaluation including computer-based M&amp;E systems alongside other customized tools for specific needs and solutions. He has strengths in stakeholder management and coordination. He would always work in an environments demanding for results, independent work and pressure while adhering to set timeline and work ethics. Overall, Mr. Onditi has been in research, strategy and advisory positions in both private, NGO&rsquo;s and public institutions assisting institutions to design ICT systems and strategies, Knowledge Management as well as Monitoring. Evaluation, research and Learning strategies for improved decision&rsquo;s.</p>'),
