(1941, NULL, NULL, 2119, 'not applicable', 'Associate', 'odiwuoraustine@yahoo.com', 'Kenyan', '29598185', '81200', 'Mombasa', 'Mombasa', '0708836422', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: small;\"><strong>INTRODUCTION STATEMENT</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: small;\">My name is Odiwuor Austine, a graduate with a degree in environmental science from Egerton University, Nakuru &ndash; Kenya. I am currently a lecturer ate Kenya Coast National Polytechnic, Mombasa &ndash; Kenya, training and assessing students who are pursuing diploma course in Environmental Science and Technology.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: small;\">My zeal towards environmental management has pushed me to establish a number of initiatives within the polytechnic. I was able to start a students&rsquo; environmental club that is currently implementing the United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization (UNESCO) project of GREENING TVET (technical vocational education and training) globally in TVET instituions. We have been able to create awareness in communities by marking environmental events and days such as World Environmental Day of 2018, World Oceans Day of 2018, International Day of Forests of 2019, Blue Economy Conference of 2018 and blue economy symposium on 17/05/2018 at Kenya School of Government Mombasa Campus. We have also engaged stakeholders in green symposium at the polytechnic to educate and create awareness on sustainable development and its goals, and greening concepts. We take part in street and beach cleaning and tree planting campaigns. Not to mention that we are part of Mombasa County national tree planting committee under the office of county commissioner. We are planning to collaborate with learning institutions (primary and secondary) in Mombasa County to disseminate information and create environmental stewards for the future generations.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: small;\">Becoming a member of Environmental Institute of Kenya, I am optimistic that the membership will provide me the opportunity to network and build capacity for collaboration and to practice as an expert. My philosophy of conservation and management has always been &lsquo;involve stakeholders in decision making&rsquo; to achieve maximum desired output. &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>'),
