(2705, NULL, NULL, 2939, 'P051639259Y', 'Lead', 'info@qualefylimited.com', 'Kenyan', '25757750', '366', 'Naivasha', 'Nakuru', '0729000712', '<p>I am an environmental science graduate with over 9 years hands on experience since the year 2012. Over this period, I have held positions as environmental technologist with Polucon Services in conducting air quality assessments, noise and vibration impact assessment and overseeing health and safety matters for 4 years. Currently practicing as an environmental specialist with an International NGO promoting Environment and Climate Change programs. I am the founder of Qualefy Limited, an environmental health and safety company looking to become a NEMA designated laboratory in the field of air quality, noise and vibration and water monitoring.&nbsp;</p>'),
(2706, NULL, NULL, 2940, 'A000213225X', 'Lead', 'm.tole@pu.ac.ke', 'Kenyan', '7113774', 'P. O. Box 195 - 80108', 'Kilifi', 'Kilifi', '+254 733 812799', '<p>Prof Mwakio Tole is Professor of Environmental Geochemistry at Pwani University, teaching undergraduate and postgraduate students in the Department of Environmental Sciences since 2009. Among the courses taught is the Masters EIA course. From 2003 to 2009, Prof Tole was at Kenyatta University, Department of Environmental Sciences, and Chairman of the Department. From 1989 to 2003, Prof Tole was at the School of Environmental Studies, Moi University, teaching environmental issues to Masters and PhD students, including Environmental Impact Assessment. He was editor of the book, \"Environmental Impact Assessment in Kenya: Theory and Practice\" published by the African Academy of Sciences in 1997. From 2001 to 2003 Prof Tole was a member of the National Environmental Management Council, and from 2007 to 2010 a member of the Board of the National Environment Management Authority. From 2004 to 2007 Prof Tole was a coopted member of the Kenya Institute of Environmental Assessment. Prof Tole was registered as a Lead EIA expert in 2004 (Registration Number 0052)</p>'),
