(3247, NULL, NULL, 3527, 'P051539461S', 'Lead', 'muirurip08@gmail.com', 'Kenya', '24718010', '00100', 'Nairobi', 'Kiambu', '+254721620221', '<p>I am an experienced hydrologist, drilling fluids, and WASH expert with a diverse background spanning over 10 years in water resources and environmental management, oil and gas development, and the humanitarian sector. I have a master&rsquo;s degree in Water Resources and Environmental Management focused on the application of remote sensing and GIS in hydrology and WREM from ITC, University of Twente, and a BSc degree in Water Engineering from Kenyatta University. I am a registered hydrologist, graduate engineer, and EIA &amp; Audit Associate expert.</p>\r\n<p>I am experienced in oilfield drilling and exploration, water resources development and management, EPM, emergency and post-emergency WASH programming, borehole drilling and prospecting (3D and 2D geophysical Resistivity surveys for geotechnical surveys, tomography, aquifer mapping and&nbsp;groundwater exploration), and environmental impact assessment.</p>\r\n<p>I worked for Schlumberger as a drilling fluids engineer in the first phase of the Tullow Oil exploration and appraisal program in Kenya, and drilled on ten exploratory wells and developed five completion wells in the Turkana Oil Field:Twiga2/2A, Agete-1, Ngamia-4, 5, 6, 7, 8, Amosing-1,3, Ekales-1, Cheptuket-1, Badada-1 and Sala-3 in Wajir. I am conversant with various mud engineering applications, oil and gas tools, and drilling fluid formulations: water, oil, and synthetic-based mud. He has managed and coordinated a spectrum of operations and field personnel and is versed in project planning, management, drilling fluids inventory management and QHSE. He has worked for OXFAM, Feed the Children, water consultants and companies in different capacities. At Feed the Children, he was instrumental in rolling out FTC livelihoods empowerment program in Samburu and Turkana counties and developed several donor-funding proposals.</p>\r\n<p>Currently, I am involved in carrying out hydrological and feasibility studies of water pans and dams in Machakos County. I was also part of the team that developed a Progressive Cavity Pump (PCP) training manual and sourced the PCP trainers for KIPYA Africa Drilling Solutions in May 2018 and was instrumental in conjointly developing a geo-referenced national borehole repository (Borehole Map of Kenya) for Water Resources Authority with KIPYA.</p>'),
