ity.</strong></li>\r\n<li>Maintained frequent&nbsp;<strong>backstopping of the WB supported projects, capacity building of the stakeholders and dialogue with clients to ensure sustainability issues.</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Previously worked in 3 World Bank/Government of Kenya supported projects for 10 years as the environmental specialist. I also has worked as a Civil Servant in the Government of Kenya in various capacities for a period spanning 12 years.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Mr. Kilaka has also experience in the <strong>Developing Countries</strong>: Indonesia - Cidanau Watershed Catchment: Ecosystem Services, ICRAF, South East Asia Regional Office (July &ndash; November 2014) as a Associate Researcher &ndash; &ldquo;Study PES Concept and application on Forest Conservation and on on-farm SLM Practices and Incentives&rdquo;. In Rwanda, he did a Consultancy on &ldquo;Assessment of Existing Market information for Sustainable Land Management (SLM)&rdquo; - (February &ndash; April 2014) while in Ghana he was a Task Team member in the implementation of the Country Investment Framework May 2013. In all these ocassions, NEMA has been a close collaborator. Secondly, it was because of the NEMA Lead Expert Registration that i managed a job with the World Bank.</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>He is a member of the Institute of Kenya Environmentalists; Kenya Society of Agricultural Professionals and National Environment Management Authority - Lead Expert.</p>'),
