(3689, NULL, NULL, 3994, 'A007059169F', 'Lead', '', 'Kenyan', '29812657', 'N/A', 'Kinango', 'Kwale', '0705423881', '<p>Hamisi Zuma Madilo is an Environmental, Occupational Health and Safety Expert. He has a degree in Environmental Conservations and Natural Resources management from University of Nairobi, Kenya and Certificate in Safety and Health Committee Training Level 1/3 from Kaileys Consortium, Integrated Environmental Impact Assessment &amp; Audit from University of Nairobi. ArcGIS from University of Nairobi. He has done graduate training programme at Base Titanium Kwale Mining Company. He has published different research projects sponsered by NGOs.</p>\r\n<p>He is also trained in Advanced and Basic first aid and firefighting, emergency response, job safety observation and analysis, incident investigation, height safety, and confined space work.</p>\r\n<p>He has Research Reports Writing skills, Communication Skills, Planning and Organizing, Systems knowledge and supervisor desk file recordkeeping skills.</p>\r\n<p>He has experience in implementing Environmental Management System, carrying out ecological monitoring, environmental radiation monitoring, dust monitoring, noise monitoring, water quality monitoring, and waste monitoring and inspections at workplace. In addition, he also carries out an environmental impact assessment and audits, soil and water sampling, creating and analysis maps. He has also carried out work process hazard identification and conducted workplace health and safety risk assessments.</p>\r\n<p>He is registered with NEMA as Environmental Impact Assessment/Environmental Audit associate expert (Reg. No. 10382) and is familiar with Kenyan Environmental, Health and Safety legislation, and international best practice</p>'),
