(3938, NULL, NULL, 4267, 'NA', 'Lead', 'stanleynjau@gmail.com', 'Kenyan', '14656538', '1086', 'KIKUYU', 'Kiambu ', '+254722297836', '<p>Stanley has 20 + years of experience in emergencies, humanitarian, and development leadership gained over years working with international consulting engineering firms, International NGOs, and UN Agencies in different missions abroad spearheading multimillion-dollar Water Sanitation &amp; Hygiene (WASH), Shelter/Infrastructural and Environmental Sustainability programs in various countries in Sub-Sahara Africa and the Middle East region focusing on displaced population (refugees, IDPs) as well as host countries and working closely with respective other partners, National and regional governments, respective line ministries, and local communities in rural, peri-urban, urban settings.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Credible history of improving and providing practical solutions in Water Sanitation &amp; Hygiene (WASH), Shelter &amp; Infrastructure NFIs, and Environmental projects as well as formulating and presenting tangible solutions to the Senior leadership and policymakers for informed decision-making including strategic negotiation and partnership with private sectors and governments (Nationals, County, line ministries and other government state entities). Am a skilled negotiator and have brokered numerous agreements, which have produced win-win outcomes.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Over the last decade, I have developed an interest in Environmental Sustainability programming, particularly in Energy, WASH, Shelter, and Infrastructure programs to deliver sustainable and environmentally sensitive outcomes, and to that end. I am an Environmental Impact Assessment and Environmental Auditor (EIA/EA) and registered with National Environmental Management Authority (NEMA) in Kenya as a licensed and practicing EIA/EA Lead Expert and have conducted dozens of EIA/EA in different sectors &ndash; WASH, infrastructures, waste management, irrigation, renewable energy, etc. In addition, am a Certified Change Management Professional (CCMP&trade;) with proven success in leading complex and sensitive organizational change initiatives. Possesses comprehensive experience in developing and managing projects/programs funded by various donors - UNHCR, UNICEF, UNOCHA, UNHABITAT, EU, ECHO, PRM, FCDO (before DFID), KfW, BMZ, DANIDA, SIDA, GAC, USAID/OFDA, SDC, SHF, Various foundations and MoFA (various foreign governments), Am a full member of several International and National professional associations/societies.</p>'),
