(3940, NULL, NULL, 4269, 'Not applicable', 'Lead', '', 'Japanese', 'TZ1386255', '2596-00621', 'Nairobi', 'Nairobi', '0714195880', '<p>My name is Naoto Shibui and I am an environmental practitioner passionate in sustainability that has been trained and working principally as a researcher / consultant in different environmental fields through diverse projects both nationally and internationally.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>My academic background is in biology where I obtained both a Bachelor&rsquo;s and Master&rsquo;s degree from Georg-August-University, Goettingen, Germany &amp; Philipps University, Marburg, Germany.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The areas of my professional expertise range from environmental impact assessment (EIA), environmental monitoring, feasibility studies, initial survey, regulation investigation and policy trend analysis to technical assessments and project management in bilateral and multilateral environmental projects while I spent over 10 years of my professional experience in Kenya.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In terms of environmental regulation &amp; policy analysis, I have been conducting regulatory research for EIA regulations of 47 African countries which provided me a critical mind and a sharp insight to analyse complex EIA regulations of each country. In the area of environmental monitoring, I have been responsible for the design, supervision, result analysis and reporting of the baseline &amp; periodic monitoring activities for various environmental parameters, such as soil, seabed sediment, surface and ground water, air, noise and waste. These professional experiences enhanced my ability to objectively evaluate the environmental impact and also my creativity to develop the most compliant and environmentally suitable alternatives under different project limitations.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Through these academic and professional experiences, I am confident about my critical skills as an environmental practitioner, and my goal is to further expand my area of practice, especially in the area of EIA to contribute to the environmental sustainability of the world we live in. As a part of this process, I would like to become a member of the Environmental Institute of Kenya.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Yours faithfully,</p>\r\n<p>Naoto Shibui</p>'),
(3941, NULL, NULL, 4270, 'Not applicable', 'Lead', '', 'Japanese', 'TZ1335531', '2596-00621', 'Nairobi', 'Nairobi', '0701209256', '<p>My name is Yumi Yamane and I am an environmental practitioner passionate in sustainability that has been trained and working principally as a researcher / consultant in different environmental fields, including conservation field.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>My academic background is in conservation where I obtained my degree of Doctor (PhD) of Area Studies in the Field of African Area Studies from the Graduate School of Asian and African Studies of Kyoto University, Japan.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The areas of my professional expertise range Conservation Ecology, African Area Study, Wildlife Management, Natural history and conservation of African Leopard among others, with a professional experience of over 10 years.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In terms of environmental regulatory investigation, I have been conducting extensive research for EIA regulations of more than 15 African countries. In the area of environmental monitoring, I have been supporting the analysis and reporting of the periodic monitoring activities for various environmental parameters, such as soil, seabed sediment, surface and ground water, air, noise, as well as monitoring of the contamination level of fish and changes in fishery resources. Additionally, I have also supported the monitoring of marine mammals&rsquo; behaviours in bilateral environmental projects.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Through these academic and professional experiences, I am confident about my critical skills as an environmental practitioner with a deep understanding of conservation principles and maintaining a healthy balance with economic development, and my goal is to further expand my area of practice, especially in the area of environmental sustainability. As a part of this process, I would like to become a member of the Environmental Institute of Kenya.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Yours f