(5035, NULL, NULL, 5411, NULL, 'Associate', 'x', 'Kenyan', '29203999', '64723-00620', 'Nairobi', 'Nairobi', '727720651', '<p>Chris Kimanga is an associate environmental expert and civil engineering professional with&nbsp; expertise in civil engineering, project planning and development that spans over 8 years both in the private and public sectors. Chris&rsquo; key areas of experience include project feasibility, planning, development, monitoring and evaluation of public and private infrastructure.</p>\r\n<p>Currently, He serves as&nbsp;a Civil and Structural Engineer at La Femme Engineering Services Limited, an engineering consulting firm based in Nairobi. At La Femme, Chris successfully designed and supervised high impact construction projects in renewable energy, transport, education, health care, security, governance, and WASH (Water, Sanitation and Hygiene) for clients such as UNICEF, WFP and Adam Smith International.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Chris also serves as a Board Member at the Kenya Green Building Society (KGBS), providing technical expertise on how to effectively engage National and County Governments in mainstreaming green building practices in their policies, operations and infrastructure development programs.</p>\r\n<p>Chris has a Bachelor of Science in Civil Engineering from the University of Nairobi as well as certifications in Project Management Professional (PMP), Certified Public Accounting (CPA) and Environmental Impact Assessment (EIA).</p>'),
