(5065, NULL, NULL, 5443, 'N/A', 'Associate', 'x', 'Kenyan', '24446145', '254', 'Nairobi', 'Kenya', '720727287', '<p>Dr. Gordon Ocholla is an environmental management expert with interest in research, training and policy analysis on climate change, circular &amp; green economy, water &amp; sanitation, and integrated environmental resources management. He works as a tutorial fellow at Mount Kenya University, Department of Social and Development Studies. His research work focuses on&nbsp;urban&nbsp;political ecology; socio-technical innovations in urban WASH services; climate justice;&nbsp;trans-boundary biodiversity conservation&nbsp;and indigenous knowledge systems (IKS) in resource management.</p>\r\n<p>Dr. Ocholla holds a PhD in Environmental Planning &amp; Management from Kenyatta University in Kenya.&nbsp;<em>His doctoral study was sponsored by the&nbsp;</em>German Academic Exchange Service&nbsp;(DAAD) scholarship and a research grant from the British Institute in Eastern Africa (BIEA).&nbsp; As part of his doctoral study, he participated in research fellowships at the Swiss Federal Institute of Aquatic Science and Technology-Eawag&nbsp;(Switzerland)&nbsp;and&nbsp;University of Bayreuth&nbsp;(Germany). His current focus is to apply his expertise in mentoring learners and sensitizing society towards the realization of Agenda 2063 of the Africa We Want - Particularly Goal #7 (environmentally sustainable and climate resilient economies).</p>'),
