(5331, '2024-06-02 18:44:19', '2024-06-02 18:44:19', 5742, NULL, 'Student', 'agagi.vic@yahoo.com', NULL, '30835331', '2ND AVENUE KENYATTA ROAD, JUJA', 'NAIROBI', 'KENYA', '0768463484', 'Victor Agagi is a graduate of Environmental Horticulture and a current student of MSc Landscape Planning and Conservation, JKUAT. He is passionate about conservation efforts from a social-ecological systems viewpoint. His aim is to work with researchers, policymakers, practitioners, and local communities to establish the intricate interplay of history, governance, livelihoods, ecology, and conservation, and find long-term solutions to the conservation challenges.'),
(5337, '2024-06-07 01:07:44', '2024-06-07 13:23:45', 5756, '2626', 'Non - Practicing Lead Member', 'jmaniafu@yahoo.com', 'kenyan', '22306319', 'Box 385', 'BUNGOMA', 'Bungoma', '0724430437', 'I am an environmentalist with over 19 years, an Alumni of DANIDA Fellowship, a graduate of Kenyatta University and University of Nairobi with experience in environmental governance at local level, environmental planning and management in natural resource, climate change, regional and urban planning, strategic environmental impact assessment, environmental Impact assessment, environmental auditing, waste management, air quality monitoring, natural resource use conflict management, community mobilization, advocacy and environmental awareness creation, mining and associated social economic and environmental aspects, conducting surveillance and targeted inspections, environmental enforcement and compliance, social safeguards, conducting environmental research and policy formulation having been admitted graduated in 2005. I have worked in the Private Sector, as an environmental officer and education officer. Am a registered environmental Lead expert no 1789. I have extensive experience in environmental management in mining sector, tree growing, oil and gas sector and urban development. I have undertaken and participated in many environmental Impact assessment projects both private and public for over 10 years. I have solid experience advising both the Government and various private sector players on various matters including legal requirements on natural resources management, climate change sectors, mining, and water resource sector. I have worked and engaged with several stakeholders from various disciplines and backgrounds including Government, private sector, communities, academia, civil societies, Non-Governmental Organizations, communities, development partners and donors.'),
